A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Mercer University and recognizing February 20, 2025, as Mercer University
2 Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, founded in 1833 and moved to Macon in 1871, Mercer University has provided
4 192 years of distinguished educational service in Georgia, establishing itself as a dynamic
5 and comprehensive center of undergraduate, graduate, and professional education; and
6 WHEREAS, Mercer University enrolls more than 9,200 students across 12 schools and
7 colleges, offering diverse academic programs in liberal arts and sciences, law, pharmacy,
8 medicine, health professions, business, engineering, education, theology, music, nursing, and
9 professional advancement while fostering a culture of excellence in teaching, learning,
10 research, and service; and
11 WHEREAS, the Georgia House Speaker's Chief of Staff Terry England serves as a Mercer
12 University Trustee, and numerous Mercer University alumni hold esteemed leadership
13 positions in the Georgia House of Representatives; and
